{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17611682","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17611682"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:14:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:14:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16237"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16237","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16237"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.62,0.27,0.12,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8928"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67621"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8928"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16237"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53073"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"262"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7017"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21245"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21249"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22658"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67621","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67621"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 22-year-old woman has a lump excised from her left breast. The microscopic examination of the specimen shows a well-circumscribed lesion with the following features:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBiphasic proliferation of stromal and epithelial elements\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECompressed ductal structures arranged in slit-like spaces\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESurrounding proliferation of dense fibrous connective tissue\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENo cellular atypia or increased mitotic activity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely histological diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Fibroadenoma","Fibrocystic change","Intraductal papilloma","Phyllodes tumour","Sclerosing adenosis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe histological features described are classic for a \u003Cstrong\u003Efibroadenoma\u003C/strong\u003E. These benign tumours show a characteristic biphasic pattern with compressed ductal elements surrounded by proliferating fibrous stroma, creating a well-circumscribed mass.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhyllodes tumour\u003C/strong\u003E shows a leaf-like architecture with more prominent stromal overgrowth and increased cellularity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntraductal papilloma\u003C/strong\u003E shows arborizing fibrovascular cores with epithelial proliferation within a duct\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFibrocystic change\u003C/strong\u003E typically shows cyst formation, apocrine metaplasia, and stromal fibrosis without the biphasic pattern\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESclerosing adenosis\u003C/strong\u003E shows proliferation of terminal duct lobular units with distortion but maintains a lobular architecture\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFibroadenomas are the most common solid breast lesions in young women. Their well-circumscribed nature and lack of cellular atypia are important features that help distinguish them from malignant lesions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fibroadenomas are benign breast tumours composed of both stromal and epithelial elements.","Histologically, fibroadenomas show a characteristic pattern of compressed ductal elements surrounded by fibrous stromal tissue.","Fibroadenomas typically present in young women aged 20-30 years and are the most common solid breast lesions in this age group."],"references":["Ramala SR, Chandak S, Chandak MS, et al. A Comprehensive Review of Breast Fibroadenoma: Correlating Clinical and Pathological Findings. Cureus. 2023 Dec 5;15(12):e49948."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53073"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16237"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53073","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53073"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-06T08:45:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-06T08:45:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8928"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67621"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/ta